1:
Give ear to my prayer, God;
\q and do not hide yourself from my plea.
\q

2:
Pay attention to me and answer me;
\q I have no rest in my troubles
\q

7:
See, then I would wander far away;
\q I would stay in the wilderness.
\qs Selah\qs*

10:
Day and night they go about on its walls;
\q iniquity and mischief are in the middle of it.
\q

15:
Let death come suddenly on them;
\q let them go down alive to Sheol,
\q for wickedness is where they live, right among them.

17:
In the evening, morning and at noonday I complain and moan;
\q he will hear my voice.
\q

20:
My friend has raised his hands against those who were at peace with him;
\q he has not respected the covenant that he had.
\q

22:
Place your burdens on Yahweh, and he will sustain you;
\q he will never allow a righteous person to totter.
\q

23:
But you, God, will bring the wicked down into the pit of destruction;
\q bloodthirsty and deceitful men will not live even half as long as others,
\q but I will trust in you.
